2021-22 Senior Free Dance. 

“It's amazing, Molly. The love inside, you take it with you.” - Sam Wheat (Patrick Swayze) from the movie ‘Ghost’ (1990).

Canadian Ice Dancers Lily Hensen and Nathan Lickers rehearse their 2021-22 Senior Free Dance to the soundtrack of Ghost ahead of competing at the Championnats Québécois d'été. Lily and Nathan are coached by Scott Moir at the Ice Academy of Montreal - Ontario. Their Free Dance is choreographed by Sheri Moir and Scott Moir, with music design by Hugo Chouinard, and additional composition by Karl Hugo. Filmed in August 2021 at Centre Gadbois in Montreal, QC by Jordan Cowan of On Ice Perspectives.

__⛸ @LilyHensen & @Nathan.Lickers
__🎥 by Jordan @oniceperspectives
__🎵 Unchained Melody @MarcMartel
__🎓 Coached by @ScottMoir14
__👣 Choreo by Sheri Moir @ScottMoir14

__📍 Centre Gadbois, Montreal, QC

Featuring @TessTerpos @WesleyRuckerCampbell.
❄️
Something I love doing is making multi-camera, multi-pass video archives of great live skating performances. I had the opportunity this month with @TheNextIceAge in Ocean City, Maryland. Talia and I spent a week with the cast as they performed part of their ten week summer show at The Carousel Hotel, just steps from the bright and sunny beach. Thank you Nathan Birch for the invitation, and I can’t wait to show you the entire show!
🏖
By the way, if you’re close to The Carousel Hotel in Ocean City, The Next Ice Age performs their free show at 6:30pm every day except Fridays, with their final performance on Sunday September 5th!
❄️
__⛸ @TessTerpos @WesleyRuckerCampbell
__🎥 Video by Jordan @oniceperspectives
__🎵 “Open Arms” by @JourneyMusicOfficial
__🎪 Show created by Nathan Birch @nathanialskitchen
__📍 @CarouselHotel Ocean City, MD

2021-22 Senior Free Dance. 

“It's amazing, Molly. The love inside, you take it with you.” - Sam Wheat (Patrick Swayze) from the movie ‘Ghost’ (1990).

Canadian Ice Dancers Lily Hensen and Nathan Lickers rehearse their 2021-22 Senior Free Dance to the soundtrack of Ghost ahead of competing at the Championnats Québécois d'été. Lily and Nathan are coached by Scott Moir at the Ice Academy of Montreal - Ontario. Their Free Dance is choreographed by Sheri Moir and Scott Moir, with music design by Hugo Chouinard, and additional composition by Karl Hugo. Filmed in August 2021 at Centre Gadbois in Montreal, QC by Jordan Cowan of On Ice Perspectives.

@icegirlash and Timothy LeDuc’s 2021-22 Senior Pairs Short Program is now available on On Ice Perspectives’ YouTube channel. It was meant to premiere with their debut performance this weekend at Cranberry Cup. Unfortunately, in the week between filming this and leaving for competition, Ashley was exposed to COVID-19, and despite being a world class athlete, fully-vaccinated, and wearing masks with her students, she was still affected enough to require hospitalization and miss their first competition since Worlds. The good news is that Ash is already doing better, testing negative again and will soon be out of quarantine and back to preparing for her and Tim’s next competition.

It’s important for us all to remember that COVID-19 is still a serious and deadly disease, not just for the unvaccinated, or immunocompromised, but also for the people in our lives we’d least expect. To protect them and get to the end of this pandemic, we need to stay vigilant with masks in crowded spaces, follow social distancing guidelines, and most importantly, get you and your loved ones vaccinated to protect against the worst side effects and reduce the spread of variants. I myself choose all three, and am grateful for the opportunity, and privilege, to travel and film and bring skating to everyone who cannot experience it in person right now. Stay safe, on and off the ice. - Jordan @oniceperspectives
